DURBAN, November 23 – Thousands of football fans are expected to converge at Durban’s New Beach for the fan park, when the Telkom Knockout semifinal between Kaizer Chiefs and Orlando Pirates is played at Moses Mabhida Stadium on Saturday. The fan park will be an alternative public viewing venue for football supporters and members of the public. Durban’s New Beach fan park is an opportunity for those who have not managed to get their hands on the tickets for the Soweto Derby. The public viewing will start at noon, three hours before the game starts at 3pm. Other public viewing venues will include Max’s Lifestyle in Umlazi, Artizen in KwaMashu and Comfort Zone in Clermont.  (ANA)